No action of mans deviſing may be ſaid to ſignifie the cleanſing our conſcience
                           •
                         from Sin, but my argument refers to the whole ſignification of baptiſm, and particularly the burial of Chriſt and others with him, Rom. 6 we are buried with him in baptiſm, and the Scripture cannot be broken, therefore baptiſm muſt ſo be performed as to ſignifie theſe things:
